              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3d50gh6v/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>the Hebrew will be a great desideratum, but the congregation<lb/>\n                                        will not be expected to do more than they bargain for\n                                        and<lb/> it will depend on the popularity and abilities of\n                                        the<lb/> successful candidate to make more by “Matanots” or\n                                        by<lb/> teaching our youth. (he is also entitled to all\n                                        marriage<lb/> fees) You remark in your letter “Should\n                                        you<lb/> “gentlemen decide upon judging of my capability\n                                        personally<lb/> “I should in all likelihood bring with me\n                                        such certificates<lb/> “as to meet with your entire\n                                        confidence, in that case<lb/> “I should much like to receive\n                                        a minute account of the<lb/> “duties attached to the\n                                        Hazanship before I undertake so<lb/> “expensive a\n                                        voyage”</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I have already given you an outline<lb/> of the\n                                        duties of the office but the Board can take no<lb/> action\n                                        or give any advice as to whether you should come<lb/> out or\n                                        not, they are acting in this instance simply as<lb/> the <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">mouth piece</hi> of the\n                                        Congregation in announcing the exis<lb/>=ting vacancy, the\n                                        forthcoming election &amp; in corresponding<lb/> with\n                                        parties interested, but the election is made by<lb/> the\n                                        members of the congregation at a general meeting<lb/> and\n                                        not by the Board, it would no doubt be very<lb/> agreeable\n                                        to be able to see and hear the candidates &amp;<lb/> judge\n                                        personally of their qualifications, but as no provision<lb/>\n                                        has been made to pay the <sic>travelling</sic> expenses of\n                                        such<lb/> as wished to come on trial it must be left to the<lb/>\n                                        <sic>judgement</sic> or inclination of the parties\n                                        themselves whether<lb/> to come or not, Under all\n                                        circumstances however<lb/> it will be very important to have\n                                        from the best<lb/> sources the most ample testimonials of\n                                        capacity and<lb/> standing.  I am dear Sir</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(8)\">yours Very Respy</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(9)\"><persName role=\"author\">A: Hart</persName>,\n                                        Parnass K.K.M.S.</p>\n                              <p>To <persName>Mr S. Morais</persName></p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                                        <placeName>10 Bevis Marks</placeName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(2)\">\n                                        <placeName>London</placeName>\n                              </p>\n                    </body>\n          </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
